 To automate code generation for a Python function that determines whether a number is prime, we can use a templating library such as Jinja2 or Mako. Here's an example using Jinja2:

1. Create a new Jinja2 template file, for example, `prime_checker.j2`.

```jinja2
{% macro generate_code(n) %}
    {% if n <= 1 %}
        return false;
    {% else %}
        {% for i in range(2, int(n ** 0.5) + 1) %}
            {% if n % i == 0 %}
                return false;
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
        return true;
    {% endif %}
{% endmacro %}
```
